"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses library scikit-learn. The issue lies in the way the ColumnTransformer is used with the Pipeline. The ColumnTransformer is correctly defined, but the GaussianNB algorithm in the Pipeline does not support the output of the ColumnTransformer which is a numpy array with more than 2 features for the OneHotEncoder part. GaussianNB expects non-negative feature values but OneHotEncoder outputs 0s and 1s which can be considered as indicators of categories. However, the MinMaxScaler outputs float values which can be negative and can be considered as non-indicator features.\",\n  \"patch\": \"26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', GaussianNB(var_smoothing=1e-9))\\nHowever, a better solution would be to use a different algorithm that supports mixed data types, such as Decision Trees or Random Forests.\\n26c26\\n< ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n---\\n> ('algo', DecisionTreeClassifier())\"\n}"